<node id="AI system">
  <data key="d0">AI system</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">An AI system is a machine-based system designed to operate autonomously and infer outputs based on input received to influence physical or virtual environments.&lt;SEP&gt;AI system is a type of technology designed to perform specific tasks based on data and AI principles.&lt;SEP&gt;AI system refers to systems within the meaning of Regulation (EU) 2024/1689.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-afaeda77e104462626d5a0e5a16d6f4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b23dceb665491f7cc28993744bf6190&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5303a356a94e477f040c55c8fb0446c1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828336</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-risk AI system">
  <data key="d0">High-risk AI system</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">High-risk AI system is a specific type of AI system regulated under this directive.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-afaeda77e104462626d5a0e5a16d6f4e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828336</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="General-purpose AI model">
  <data key="d0">General-purpose AI model</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">General-purpose AI model is a type of AI system with broad applications.&lt;SEP&gt;General-purpose AI models are regulated under this directive.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-afaeda77e104462626d5a0e5a16d6f4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b23dceb665491f7cc28993744bf6190</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828336</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Parliament">
  <data key="d0">European Parliament</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Parliament has the power to revoke delegated acts.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Parliament is one of the two main legislative bodies in the European Union and receives reports and assessments from the Commission.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Parliament is one of the overseers for the implementation and review of AI regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-afaeda77e104462626d5a0e5a16d6f4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06bc0ddf887512f18d0e6f10df7767fa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Council">
  <data key="d0">Council</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Council can also revoke delegated acts.&lt;SEP&gt;The Council is one of the two main legislative bodies in the European Union and receives reports and assessments from the Commission.&lt;SEP&gt;The Council is one of the overseers for the implementation and review of AI regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-afaeda77e104462626d5a0e5a16d6f4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06bc0ddf887512f18d0e6f10df7767fa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Public Authorities">
  <data key="d0">Public Authorities</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Public Authorities are governmental bodies responsible for law enforcement and other public services.&lt;SEP&gt;Public Authorities are government bodies that use AI systems and have specific obligations related to registration.&lt;SEP&gt;Public authorities are intended users of high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Public Authorities are entities, such as law enforcement or immigration authorities, that may use AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-afaeda77e104462626d5a0e5a16d6f4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eafdecc945c96231c70d9a52d9148ae9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2f70e1025ba333d8cca73e6ed68029e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Implementation Date">
  <data key="d0">Implementation Date</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The implementation dates are mentioned, such as 2 August 2027, 2 August 2030, and others.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-afaeda77e104462626d5a0e5a16d6f4e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Delegation of Power">
  <data key="d0">Delegation of Power</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Delegation of power is mentioned in Article 97.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-afaeda77e104462626d5a0e5a16d6f4e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Market Surveillance Authorities">
  <data key="d0">Market Surveillance Authorities</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Market Surveillance Authorities are regulatory bodies responsible for ensuring the conformity and compliance of high-risk AI systems with relevant market regulations, including the AI Regulation. These authorities are mandated to oversee the deployment of AI systems and are informed by deployers about incidents. They have the power to access source code, conduct investigations, and cooperate with other authorities. Market Surveillance Authorities are also responsible for enforcing the reporting obligations and ensuring compliance with EU regulations within the Member States. They may cooperate with the Board and are mentioned as entities that can request support from the Scientific Panel. Overall, these authorities play a crucial role in evaluating AI systems and ensuring their safety and compliance with the regulatory framework.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9bbabb917a8fd4d1cab0f28da3292879&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49852a3ba29135f33f5a66d5530afe75&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f37fb5090b015fdcce5136a4e131a7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b09e19ff232fc74f764b77ba6bcc3f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ba7997e7cc9a9c81f53126131569e4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f39b62663d19c447e94b4bea8e9c4db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ff9251c686ac1ddd5ef4f93316b9a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-351f07fc1cfb91436e9dffcf5c8e88df</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Data Protection Supervisor">
  <data key="d0">European Data Protection Supervisor</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Data Protection Supervisor (EDPS) is an independent agency within the European Union, responsible for protecting the rights of individuals concerning the processing of personal data. The EDPS serves as a reference for national competent authorities or market surveillance authorities for Union institutions, agencies, offices, and bodies. It oversees the application of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and other relevant data protection regulations. The EDPS can establish an AI regulatory sandbox for Union institutions and bodies, acting as a market surveillance authority. As a supervisory body, the EDPS plays a crucial role in ensuring the proper application of data protection laws across the European Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9bbabb917a8fd4d1cab0f28da3292879&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6a6be1a6e159da5602b5c2c89e742e39&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9a59e2a8b6b3ba9d239dfd8b387900e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-351f07fc1cfb91436e9dffcf5c8e88df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d3918796c66f4ec90d4e54c0693276f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b23dceb665491f7cc28993744bf6190</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Harmonised Standard">
  <data key="d0">Harmonised Standard</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Harmonised Standard is a standard as defined in Article 2(1), point (c), of Regulation (EU) No 1025/2012.&lt;SEP&gt;Harmonised standards cover the requirements or obligations set out in the Chapter, as applicable.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef9991e58e018e79ec133e41dd155972</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Common Specification">
  <data key="d0">Common Specification</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Common Specification is a technical specification as defined in Article 2, point (4) of Regulation (EU) No 1025/2012.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef9991e58e018e79ec133e41dd155972</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Training Data">
  <data key="d0">Training Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Training Data is used to train AI systems by fitting their learnable parameters.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Validation Data">
  <data key="d0">Validation Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Validation Data is used to evaluate the trained AI system and tune its parameters to prevent underfitting or overfitting.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Validation Data Set">
  <data key="d0">Validation Data Set</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Validation Data Set is a separate data set used for evaluating the trained AI system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Testing Data">
  <data key="d0">Testing Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Testing Data is used to independently evaluate the AI system before placing it on the market.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Input Data">
  <data key="d0">Input Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Input Data is provided to or directly acquired by an AI system to produce an output.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64f96fb4c623fd44d4b9931460dfb273</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Biometric Data">
  <data key="d0">Biometric Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Biometric Data refers to personal data from physical, physiological, or behavioural characteristics such as facial images or dactyloscopic data.&lt;SEP&gt;Biometric Data are personal data collected by biometric systems, which are regulated by specific laws.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Biometric Identification">
  <data key="d0">Biometric Identification</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Biometric Identification is the automated recognition of human biometric data for establishing identity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Biometric Verification">
  <data key="d0">Biometric Verification</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Biometric Verification is the automated, one-to-one verification of a person's identity using their biometric data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Special Categories of Personal Data">
  <data key="d0">Special Categories of Personal Data</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Special Categories of Personal Data are personal data covered in Article 9(1) of Regulation (EU) 2016/679.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sensitive Operational Data">
  <data key="d0">Sensitive Operational Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Sensitive Operational Data is data related to prevention, detection, investigation, or prosecution of criminal offences.&lt;SEP&gt;Sensitive Operational Data includes confidential information about the operation of AI systems, particularly for law enforcement authorities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Emotion Recognition System">
  <data key="d0">Emotion Recognition System</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Emotion Recognition System is an AI system for identifying or inferring emotions from biometric data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Biometric Categorisation System">
  <data key="d0">Biometric Categorisation System</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Biometric Categorisation System is an AI system for categorising natural persons based on biometric data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Remote Biometric Identification System">
  <data key="d0">Remote Biometric Identification System</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Remote Biometric Identification System is an AI system for identifying natural persons without active involvement and typically using biometric data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Real-Time Remote Biometric Identification System">
  <data key="d0">Real-Time Remote Biometric Identification System</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Real-Time Remote Biometric Identification System is a Remote Biometric Identification System with instant identification and limited short delays.&lt;SEP&gt;Real-Time Remote Biometric Identification System is a system used for biometric identification in publicly accessible spaces for law enforcement purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Post-Remote Biometric Identification System">
  <data key="d0">Post-Remote Biometric Identification System</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Post-Remote Biometric Identification System is a Remote Biometric Identification System other than a Real-Time Remote Biometric Identification System.&lt;SEP&gt;Post-Remote Biometric Identification System is a specific type of high-risk AI system used for biometric identification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Publicly Accessible Space">
  <data key="d0">Publicly Accessible Space</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Publicly Accessible Space is a physical place accessible to an undetermined number of natural persons.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Law Enforcement Authority">
  <data key="d0">Law Enforcement Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Law Enforcement Authority is the entity responsible for prevention, investigation, detection, or prosecution of criminal offences.&lt;SEP&gt;Law Enforcement Authority refers to the authority responsible for granting authorizations for the use of the system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="National Competent Authority">
  <data key="d0">National Competent Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">National Competent Authority is a notifying authority or market surveillance authority.&lt;SEP&gt;National Competent Authority is a national agency responsible for enforcing certain regulatory requirements in the Member States.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8731e04e59e27f8bf0dad80e14b80dfa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Serious Incident">
  <data key="d0">Serious Incident</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Serious Incident is defined as an incident or malfunction leading to various adverse outcomes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Personal Data">
  <data key="d0">Personal Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Personal Data is data as defined in Article 4, point (1), of Regulation (EU) 2016/679.&lt;SEP&gt;Personal Data refers to any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person covered under data protection laws.&lt;SEP&gt;Personal data refers to any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person covered by specific regulatory requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Personal data refers to any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ba7997e7cc9a9c81f53126131569e4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9a59e2a8b6b3ba9d239dfd8b387900e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73bf9d05df7f156f668cf6ea0decb52f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Non-Personal Data">
  <data key="d0">Non-Personal Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Non-Personal Data is data other than personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Profiling">
  <data key="d0">Profiling</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Profiling is the automated processing of personal data to evaluate certain personal aspects.&lt;SEP&gt;Profiling is defined as the process of profiling as per Article 4, point (4), of Regulation (EU) 2016/679.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Real-World Testing Plan">
  <data key="d0">Real-World Testing Plan</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Real-World Testing Plan describes the objectives, methodology, and scope of AI system testing.&lt;SEP&gt;A real-world testing plan is a document that outlines the objectives, methodology, geographical, population, and temporal scope, as well as monitoring, organization, and conduct of testing in real-world conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Real-world testing plans are required for the testing of high-risk AI systems outside of sandboxes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73bf9d05df7f156f668cf6ea0decb52f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sandbox Plan">
  <data key="d0">Sandbox Plan</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Sandbox Plan is a document describing activities and requirements for the testing of AI systems by a provider and competent authority.&lt;SEP&gt;A sandbox plan is a document agreed between the participating provider and the competent authority, describing objectives, conditions, timeframe, methodology, and requirements for activities within the sandbox.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Commission Decision">
  <data key="d0">Commission Decision</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Commission Decision of 24 January 2024 provides for the Commission's function in AI systems governance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 71">
  <data key="d0">Article 71</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 71 is a section in the text referring to the EU database where registration information should be secured.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 71(4) of the text refers to the registration of testing in real-world conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 71 is a clause within a Regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5974c0c87096acad0b2aac605ef8802&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89493349bc2eb2b0fa14e08d5114b0a5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chapter III">
  <data key="d0">Chapter III</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Chapter III is a section in the text with unspecified transparency obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="EU database">
  <data key="d0">EU database</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The EU database is a secure, non-public electronic database where registration information is stored.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Annex IX">
  <data key="d0">Annex IX</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex IX is a section containing specific points related to registration information.&lt;SEP&gt;Annex IX specifies the information that must be included in the Union-wide unique single identification number.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89493349bc2eb2b0fa14e08d5114b0a5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="National authorities">
  <data key="d0">National authorities</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">National authorities are regional governing bodies with authority over the use and management of AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI systems">
  <data key="d0">AI systems</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">AI systems are artificial intelligence technologies that are designed to interact with natural persons, generate synthetic content, or perform various tasks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d534e37e8a91e087b0f7afd91260337</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Natural person">
  <data key="d0">Natural person</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Natural person refers to an individual human being.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deployers">
  <data key="d0">Deployers</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Deployers are organizations that use or deploy AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Deployers are entities responsible for deploying AI systems and have various obligations under the regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;Deployers are organizations or entities that use or operate AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Deployers are individuals or entities involved in deploying AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d534e37e8a91e087b0f7afd91260337&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d3918796c66f4ec90d4e54c0693276f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Emotion recognition system">
  <data key="d0">Emotion recognition system</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">An emotion recognition system is a type of AI system designed to detect or recognize emotions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Biometric categorisation system">
  <data key="d0">Biometric categorisation system</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A biometric categorisation system is a type of AI system designed to categorize biometric data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive (EU) 2016/680">
  <data key="d0">Directive (EU) 2016/680</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive (EU) 2016/680 is a specific legal framework governing the use of AI systems in law enforcement.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive 2016/680 is a regulatory framework governing the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive (EU) 2016/680 provides conditions for competent data protection supervisory authorities.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive (EU) 2016/680 is the Regulation on Medical Devices.&lt;SEP&gt;Directive (EU) 2016/680 is a directive related to AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6a6be1a6e159da5602b5c2c89e742e39&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-612e9d6ebed2e9c1601b0ed553a37ca2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2bf04dc1138e594ddbe71572222dd4f3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulations (EU) 2016/679">
  <data key="d0">Regulations (EU) 2016/679</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation 2016/679, also known as the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), stipulates how organizations should process and protect personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
