  <data key="d0">Regulations (EU) 2018/1725</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation 2018/1725 is a framework for the administrative cooperation between Member States in law enforcement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deep fake">
  <data key="d0">Deep fake</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A deep fake is an AI-generated manipulation of visual or audio content that is intended to deceive.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Systemic risk">
  <data key="d0">Systemic risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Systemic risk refers to the risk of widespread impact on the financial system or economy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scientific panel">
  <data key="d0">Scientific panel</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A scientific panel is a group of experts who provide technical and scientific assessments and recommendations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive (EU) 2018/1725">
  <data key="d0">Directive (EU) 2018/1725</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive 2018/1725 is a framework for the administrative cooperation between Member States in law enforcement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Post-Market Monitoring Plan">
  <data key="d0">Post-Market Monitoring Plan</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Post-Market Monitoring Plan is a document to be included in technical documentation, guiding the monitoring of high-risk AI systems after market release.&lt;SEP&gt;Post-Market Monitoring Plan outlines strategies for ongoing evaluation of the AI system's performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-612e9d6ebed2e9c1601b0ed553a37ca2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bbabb917a8fd4d1cab0f28da3292879</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Implementing Act">
  <data key="d0">Implementing Act</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Implementing acts establish common specifications for requirements or obligations.&lt;SEP&gt;Implementing Acts adopted by the Commission may approve a code of practice and give it a general validity within the Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Implementing Act is an act that lays down detailed provisions for the template of the post-market monitoring plan and the list of elements to be included.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef9991e58e018e79ec133e41dd155972</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Commission">
  <data key="d0">Commission</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Commission is a governing body within the European Union that has the authority and responsibility to propose and implement EU policies and regulations, manage the day-to-day affairs of the Union, and uphold its treaties. It is a key executive branch involved in the development, implementation, and enforcement of regulatory policies, including those related to artificial intelligence (AI).

The Commission is responsible for adopting delegated acts, which include amending the list of high-risk AI systems, issuing standardisation requests, and overseeing the conformity assessment procedures for these systems. It also has the authority to issue guidelines and draw up reports, and it can enter into consultations and make decisions regarding the justification of authorizations. The Commission can designate AI models as those with systemic risk and keep the list of these models up to date. It cooperates with national competent authorities to exercise their competences and powers, ensures compliance with AI regulation, and proposes fines for violations.

In the context of the AI regulatory sandbox framework, the Commission plays a significant role in supervising and informing other Member States about AI system evaluations and actions. It also oversees processes related to the application of the AI regulation and the implementation of the expertise and capabilities in the field of AI. Additionally, it is responsible for initiating evaluations, appointing independent experts, and issuing guidelines that may be updated based on specific criteria for assessing the impact of certain AI capabilities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-037b3133eed3c3d2ae1057711af7caab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bbabb917a8fd4d1cab0f28da3292879&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-afaeda77e104462626d5a0e5a16d6f4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d317a57f8826116be7899af7bef32dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91245f3945c3d7cc7ebcd77b066b7ef9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6a6be1a6e159da5602b5c2c89e742e39&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d94f80b79b953201dabec0b31eb7d1f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b09e19ff232fc74f764b77ba6bcc3f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ba7997e7cc9a9c81f53126131569e4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38169246e9fa46f9e17ff295ac3346d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2cddb0815e714f4234b0eb77a0886db3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9a59e2a8b6b3ba9d239dfd8b387900e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e2911d860a9f8426e67a536486d6752&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd5db792306630e07b4579263bafe09f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2d5febc258257152890296838762d806&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8731e04e59e27f8bf0dad80e14b80dfa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b46993509f7f45efc7114ce53d7712a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef9991e58e018e79ec133e41dd155972&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-351f07fc1cfb91436e9dffcf5c8e88df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9aeb5afbd1a4b894acf12c446410f902&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06bc0ddf887512f18d0e6f10df7767fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f39b62663d19c447e94b4bea8e9c4db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e5d3aebe76250dd5161e123f94c06c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1594971bc99373dadcdc53ec98848241&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b23dceb665491f7cc28993744bf6190&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3235bf9304fec9e624bfd76288a19b57</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ANNEX I">
  <data key="d0">ANNEX I</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">ANNEX I is a section of the document that lists harmonisation legislation for high-risk AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 98(2)">
  <data key="d0">Article 98(2)</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 98(2) of Regulation (EU) No 1025/2012 is related to the examination procedure for implementing acts.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 98(2) is the examination procedure referred to for adopting the implementing act.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef9991e58e018e79ec133e41dd155972</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 73">
  <data key="d0">Article 73</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 73 provides a mechanism for handling situations where a deployer cannot reach the provider.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 73 is a legal provision that applies in situations where the provider of an AI system is not reachable.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 73 requires the reporting of any serious incidents during testing in real world conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 73 defines the reporting requirements for serious incidents involving high-risk AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64f96fb4c623fd44d4b9931460dfb273&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89493349bc2eb2b0fa14e08d5114b0a5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 74">
  <data key="d0">Article 74</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 74 outlines the market surveillance and control measures for AI systems in the Union market.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Compliance Obligations">
  <data key="d0">Compliance Obligations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Compliance Obligations refer to the duties established by the regulation and its related articles.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union Market">
  <data key="d0">Union Market</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Union Market refers to the market within the European Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Union Market is the marketplace covered by the regulation where high-risk AI systems are placed and sold.&lt;SEP&gt;Union Market refers to the market space across all Member States of the Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d94f80b79b953201dabec0b31eb7d1f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38169246e9fa46f9e17ff295ac3346d7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2019/1020">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2019/1020</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2019/1020 is a legal act establishing rules for the development, distribution, and use of AI systems in the EU.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2019/1020 outlines the enforcement measures for AI systems and their market surveillance.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2019/1020 is a Union regulation on AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2019/1020 is the primary legal document referenced.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2019/1020 is a European Union regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6a6be1a6e159da5602b5c2c89e742e39&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b09e19ff232fc74f764b77ba6bcc3f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5974c0c87096acad0b2aac605ef8802&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f39b62663d19c447e94b4bea8e9c4db</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union Legislative Instruments">
  <data key="d0">Union Legislative Instruments</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Union Legislative Instruments refer to the legislative instruments laying down reporting obligations equivalent to those set out in this Regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Risk Ai System">
  <data key="d0">High-Risk Ai System</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">High-Risk AI System is a system that requires stringent risk management measures and testing procedures due to its potential adverse impacts on health and safety, fundamental rights, and vulnerable groups.&lt;SEP&gt;High-Risk AI System is a category of AI systems subject to specific regulations for risk management and compliance.&lt;SEP&gt;High-Risk AI System is a specific type of AI that may have significant impacts on fundamental rights and requires assessment before deployment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-414727d1a6d237ecc9306035920d4685&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c328886326bda8019859ce49acc29cc</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Conformity Assessment Procedure">
  <data key="d0">Conformity Assessment Procedure</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Conformity assessment procedure is a process to verify compliance with regulations for high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Conformity Assessment Procedure is a set of steps or standards used to verify the conformity of products, including high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Conformity assessment procedures are methods used to ensure that AI systems meet specified requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd5db792306630e07b4579263bafe09f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e5d3aebe76250dd5161e123f94c06c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ce Marking">
  <data key="d0">Ce Marking</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">CE marking is a certification mark that indicates conformity with health, safety, and environmental protection standards for products sold within the European Economic Area.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Eu Declaration Of Conformity">
  <data key="d0">Eu Declaration Of Conformity</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">EU Declaration of Conformity is a document required for high-risk AI systems to confirm compliance with the legislation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Risk Ai System Placement On The Market">
  <data key="d0">High-Risk Ai System Placement On The Market</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Placement of a high-risk AI system on the market is a regulated activity requiring compliance with this regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI Systems">
  <data key="d0">AI Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">AI Systems are software or hardware-based systems that utilize artificial intelligence to perform tasks autonomously or with human oversight. These systems are used for various purposes, including identifying and applying corrective or preventive actions, such as biometric categorization, emotion recognition, and determining access for private and public services. AI Systems encompass a range of artificial intelligence technologies, including general-purpose models and specific high-risk applications.

Regulation plays a significant role in the development and deployment of AI Systems. They are part of the AI value chain, which includes training, development, testing, and validation. These systems are subject to codes of conduct and specific requirements aimed at ensuring trustworthiness and legal compliance. The Regulation covers the implementation and enforcement of these systems, as well as their applications in different domains, ensuring that they adhere to various national and international standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9bbabb917a8fd4d1cab0f28da3292879&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b09e19ff232fc74f764b77ba6bcc3f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eafdecc945c96231c70d9a52d9148ae9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33b3b690e83a48d4f90c85be3eebb646&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8731e04e59e27f8bf0dad80e14b80dfa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b46993509f7f45efc7114ce53d7712a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2f70e1025ba333d8cca73e6ed68029e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f39b62663d19c447e94b4bea8e9c4db</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Risk AI Systems">
  <data key="d0">High-Risk AI Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">High-Risk AI Systems are AI systems identified as posing significant risks and are subject to stringent regulation. Specifically, these systems are defined by criteria involving safety components and third-party conformity assessments. High-Risk AI Systems are generally those that pose significant risks to health, safety, or fundamental rights. These systems are often advanced and subject to specific regulations, as they carry significant risks if deployed improperly or do not meet certain requirements. In some contexts, these systems are also considered to pose significant privacy risks. High-Risk AI Systems are often covered by Union harmonisation legislation and are subject to detailed monitoring. Notably, these systems are not the subject of evaluations in paragraphs 4 and 7.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49852a3ba29135f33f5a66d5530afe75&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e2911d860a9f8426e67a536486d6752&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73bf9d05df7f156f668cf6ea0decb52f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2d5febc258257152890296838762d806&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8731e04e59e27f8bf0dad80e14b80dfa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89493349bc2eb2b0fa14e08d5114b0a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2f70e1025ba333d8cca73e6ed68029e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79168f0d206aaba1ef1cc580415c53cf</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Authorised Representative">
  <data key="d0">Authorised Representative</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Authorised representative is a person or organization appointed by a provider to act on its behalf regarding certain obligations under this regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;Authorised Representative is a person or company appointed by a manufacturer to act on their behalf in the European Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Authorised Representative is a person or entity authorised to act on behalf of a provider or deployer in the context of AI system regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5974c0c87096acad0b2aac605ef8802&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af337ff23074191f5e5e0bdd26073d1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Importers">
  <data key="d0">Importers</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Importers are entities that introduce goods into a market or territory, specifically for high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Importers are individuals or entities involved in the importation of goods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d3918796c66f4ec90d4e54c0693276f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Distributors">
  <data key="d0">Distributors</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Distributors are entities that operate in the supply chain of high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Distributors are entities that make goods available to the end customer, specifically for high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Distributors are individuals or entities involved in the distribution of goods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64f96fb4c623fd44d4b9931460dfb273&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d3918796c66f4ec90d4e54c0693276f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Importers Obligation">
  <data key="d0">Importers Obligation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Importers have specific obligations to ensure compliance with the regulation before placing a high-risk AI system on the market.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Distributors Obligation">
  <data key="d0">Distributors Obligation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Distributors have specific obligations to ensure compliance with the regulation before making a high-risk AI system available on the market.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Risk Ai System Making Available On The Market">
  <data key="d0">High-Risk Ai System Making Available On The Market</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Making a high-risk AI system available on the market is a regulated activity requiring compliance with this regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Economic and Social Committee">
  <data key="d0">European Economic and Social Committee</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Economic and Social Committee is one of the three main advisory bodies to the European Union institutions and receives reports from the Commission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 50">
  <data key="d0">Article 50</data>
  <data key="d1">statement</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 50 is also part of a regulation and defines specific terms and conditions for AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 50 of the Regulation deals with AI systems requiring additional transparency measures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5303a356a94e477f040c55c8fb0446c1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 99(1)">
  <data key="d0">Article 99(1)</data>
  <data key="d1">statement</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 99(1) refers to administrative fines for infringements of the Regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 97">
  <data key="d0">Article 97</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 97 is a section empowering the Commission to adopt delegated acts.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 97 is a part of the regulation that empowers the Commission to adopt delegated acts.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 97 is part of the Regulation and deals with the delegation of powers to the Commission.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 97 of the Regulation details the delegation of power.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e2911d860a9f8426e67a536486d6752&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2d5febc258257152890296838762d806&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06bc0ddf887512f18d0e6f10df7767fa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 101">
  <data key="d0">Article 101</data>
  <data key="d1">statement</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 101 is not applicable for the reports starting from 2 August 2025.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Section B of Annex I">
  <data key="d0">Section B of Annex I</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section B of Annex I lists sectoral Union harmonisation legislation that must be taken into account when amending the Regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Technical Documentation">
  <data key="d0">Technical Documentation</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical documentation is a crucial part of the documentation required for high-risk AI systems, as specified in Article 11 and Annex IV. It is necessary to demonstrate compliance with requirements and to provide essential information for assessment. Technical documentation includes a detailed description of the elements and processes involved in the development of an AI system, such as the training, testing, and validation procedures. It also encompasses the post-market monitoring plan, which is specified in Annex IV. Additionally, technical documentation must include comprehensive details on the AI system's monitoring, performance, risk management, and lifecycle changes. This documentation is essential for verifying and ensuring compliance with technical standards for AI systems, making it a detailed and comprehensive document that supports both the development and use of AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49852a3ba29135f33f5a66d5530afe75&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33b3b690e83a48d4f90c85be3eebb646&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5974c0c87096acad0b2aac605ef8802&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-612e9d6ebed2e9c1601b0ed553a37ca2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73bf9d05df7f156f668cf6ea0decb52f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2bf04dc1138e594ddbe71572222dd4f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4bd0831e0cdcbfe10ebd94d84d35ece&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9aeb5afbd1a4b894acf12c446410f902&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af337ff23074191f5e5e0bdd26073d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bbabb917a8fd4d1cab0f28da3292879</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828339</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation">
  <data key="d0">Regulation</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">This refers to the overarching regulation governing high-risk AI systems and their compliance requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation refers to the overall regulation being amended and supplemented by codes of practice.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation is a set of rules and requirements that must be adhered to, specifically for AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The Regulation is a legislative act that sets out the evaluation and reporting requirements for AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06bc0ddf887512f18d0e6f10df7767fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6085e0ae0998fbef84e85dbd0e87054c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Risk Levels">
  <data key="d0">Risk Levels</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Risk Levels are evaluated by the AI Office using criteria outlined in relevant Articles.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Voluntary Codes of Conduct">
  <data key="d0">Voluntary Codes of Conduct</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Voluntary Codes of Conduct promote the application of requirements set out in Chapter III, Section 2 for AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SMEs">
  <data key="d0">SMEs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">SMEs, including start-ups, are small and microenterprises that may provide technical documentation in a simplified manner.&lt;SEP&gt;SMEs (Small and Medium-sized Enterprises) are included as participants in AI regulatory sandboxes and benefit from free access under certain circumstances.&lt;SEP&gt;SMEs (Small and Medium-sized Enterprises) are businesses with a registered office or branch in the Union.&lt;SEP&gt;SMEs (Small and Medium-sized Enterprises) include start-ups and are a key focus in the implementation of the regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;SMEs refer to small and medium-sized enterprises, including start-ups.&lt;SEP&gt;Small and Medium-sized Enterprises (SMEs) are mentioned in the context of entering the market.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9a59e2a8b6b3ba9d239dfd8b387900e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-351f07fc1cfb91436e9dffcf5c8e88df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9aeb5afbd1a4b894acf12c446410f902&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06bc0ddf887512f18d0e6f10df7767fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d3918796c66f4ec90d4e54c0693276f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b46993509f7f45efc7114ce53d7712a1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union Agency">
  <data key="d0">Union Agency</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A Union Agency may be needed if identified shortcomings are found in the assessment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI Regulatory Sandbox">
  <data key="d0">AI Regulatory Sandbox</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An AI regulatory sandbox is a controlled framework set up by a competent authority for providers or prospective providers to develop, train, validate, and test innovative AI systems under regulatory supervision for a limited time in real-world conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;AI Regulatory Sandbox is a controlled environment used for testing and validating innovative AI systems before their market launch under specific regulatory conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;AI Regulatory Sandbox is a framework for testing and experimenting with AI systems to support their development and conformity assessment under the chosen Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;AI Regulatory Sandboxes are testing environments at national, regional, or joint levels established to foster innovation in AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;AI Regulatory Sandbox is a regulatory framework designed to facilitate the deployment and testing of AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;AI Regulatory Sandbox allows for supervised testing of AI systems under controlled conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f37fb5090b015fdcce5136a4e131a7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ba7997e7cc9a9c81f53126131569e4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9a59e2a8b6b3ba9d239dfd8b387900e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-351f07fc1cfb91436e9dffcf5c8e88df</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI Literacy">
  <data key="d0">AI Literacy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">AI literacy involves skills, knowledge, and understanding that enable providers, deployers, and affected persons to make informed decisions about AI systems, and to be aware of the opportunities, risks, and possible harm.&lt;SEP&gt;AI literacy ensures that staff and other relevant persons have the necessary skills, knowledge, and understanding to use AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b46993509f7f45efc7114ce53d7712a1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Real-World Testing">
  <data key="d0">Real-World Testing</data>
  <data key="d1">category</data>
  <data key="d2">Real-world testing involves the temporary testing of an AI system for its intended purpose outside laboratory or simulated environments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Subject">
  <data key="d0">Subject</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A subject is a natural person involved in real-world testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Informed Consent">
  <data key="d0">Informed Consent</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Informed consent is a subject's freely given, specific, unambiguous, and voluntary expression of willingness to participate in real-world testing, provided they are informed about all relevant aspects.&lt;SEP&gt;Informed Consent is a form of permission given by an individual after being fully informed of all relevant information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89493349bc2eb2b0fa14e08d5114b0a5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deep Fake">
  <data key="d0">Deep Fake</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A deep fake is AI-generated or manipulated image, audio, or video content that resembles existing persons, objects, places, entities, or events and appears authentic.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Widespread Infringement">
  <data key="d0">Widespread Infringement</data>
  <data key="d1">category</data>
  <data key="d2">Widespread infringement refers to acts or omissions that violate Union law and harm individual interests.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Critical Infrastructure">
  <data key="d0">Critical Infrastructure</data>
  <data key="d1">category</data>
  <data key="d2">Critical infrastructure is defined as such under Article 2, point (4), of Directive (EU) 2022/2557.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="General-Purpose AI Model">
  <data key="d0">General-Purpose AI Model</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A general-purpose AI model is a highly versatile AI model that can perform a wide range of tasks and can be integrated into various systems.&lt;SEP&gt;General-purpose AI models must meet specific requirements or comply with certain obligations.&lt;SEP&gt;A general-purpose AI model is presumed to have high impact capabilities based on the cumulative amount of computation used for its training.&lt;SEP&gt;General-Purpose AI Model is an AI model that can be used for various purposes and may or may not present systemic risks.&lt;SEP&gt;General-Purpose AI Model is an AI software developed for various purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91245f3945c3d7cc7ebcd77b066b7ef9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d94f80b79b953201dabec0b31eb7d1f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f37fb5090b015fdcce5136a4e131a7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef9991e58e018e79ec133e41dd155972&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-afaeda77e104462626d5a0e5a16d6f4e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Impact Capabilities">
  <data key="d0">High-Impact Capabilities</data>
  <data key="d1">category</data>
  <data key="d2">High-impact capabilities are advanced AI model capabilities that match or exceed the most sophisticated general-purpose AI models.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Systemic Risk">
  <data key="d0">Systemic Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Systemic risk refers to risks at the high-impact capabilities level of general-purpose AI models that impact the Union market, public health, safety, public security, fundamental rights, or society at large.&lt;SEP&gt;Systemic Risk refers to risks that can affect the entire system or market and requires special attention from providers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d94f80b79b953201dabec0b31eb7d1f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="General-Purpose AI System">
  <data key="d0">General-Purpose AI System</data>
  <data key="d1">system</data>
  <data key="d2">A general-purpose AI system is based on a general-purpose AI model and can serve various purposes both directly and through integration in other AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;General-Purpose AI System is an AI system based on a general-purpose AI model.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f37fb5090b015fdcce5136a4e131a7e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Floating-Point Operation">
  <data key="d0">Floating-Point Operation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A floating-point operation is any mathematical operation or assignment involving floating-point numbers, a subset of real numbers typically represented in computers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Downstream Provider">
  <data key="d0">Downstream Provider</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A downstream provider is a provider of an AI system (including general-purpose AI systems) that integrates AI models, regardless of the origin.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Public Authority">
  <data key="d0">Public Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Public authorities include those competent for preventing, investigating, detecting, or prosecuting criminal offences or executing criminal penalties, as well as entities exercising public authority for these purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f37fb5090b015fdcce5136a4e131a7e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Death of a Person">
  <data key="d0">Death of a Person</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Death of a person is one of the criteria for categorizing an infringement as widespread.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Serious Harm to Health">
  <data key="d0">Serious Harm to Health</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Serious harm to a person's health is another criterion for categorizing an infringement as widespread.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Disruption of Critical Infrastructure">
  <data key="d0">Disruption of Critical Infrastructure</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Serious disruption of critical infrastructure is a criterion for categorizing an infringement as widespread.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Infringement of Obligations">
  <data key="d0">Infringement of Obligations</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Infringement of obligations under Union law intended to protect fundamental rights is a criterion for categorizing an infringement as widespread.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Harm to Property or Environment">
  <data key="d0">Harm to Property or Environment</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Serious harm to property or the environment is a criterion for categorizing an infringement as widespread.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Two Member States">
  <data key="d0">Two Member States</data>
  <data key="d1">threshold</data>
  <data key="d2">An infringement is categorized as widespread if it affects at least two Member States other than the Member State where it originated.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Three Member States">
  <data key="d0">Three Member States</data>
  <data key="d1">threshold</data>
  <data key="d2">An infringement is categorized as widespread if it affects at least three Member States concurrently.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2016/679">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2016/679</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2016/679 is a piece of EU law that provides for the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data and gives effect to the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2016/679 is a legal document governing the processing of personal data and privacy.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2016/679 is a regulation concerning the protection of individuals with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2016/679 is the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), defining stringent data protection requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2016/679 is the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2016/679 is a data protection regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d534e37e8a91e087b0f7afd91260337&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9a59e2a8b6b3ba9d239dfd8b387900e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-612e9d6ebed2e9c1601b0ed553a37ca2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2bf04dc1138e594ddbe71572222dd4f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2f70e1025ba333d8cca73e6ed68029e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Directive (EU) 2022/2557">
  <data key="d0">Directive (EU) 2022/2557</data>
  <data key="d1">directive</data>
  <data key="d2">Directive (EU) 2022/2557 is an EU law that defines critical infrastructure in the context of Union law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b51ee903cf22f0e6bd5fac52ed93756</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828340</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scientific Panel">
  <data key="d0">Scientific Panel</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The scientific panel can alert the Commission about qualified alerts.&lt;SEP&gt;The Scientific Panel is a group of independent experts to support the enforcement activities under the Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;The Scientific Panel provides alerts and scientific assessments on the risks posed by AI models.&lt;SEP&gt;The scientific panel, established under Article 68, provides alerts and advice on systemic risks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-91245f3945c3d7cc7ebcd77b066b7ef9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51ee6686c61ba5ea54245e3aa87b1783&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b46993509f7f45efc7114ce53d7712a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ff9251c686ac1ddd5ef4f93316b9a8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
