<node id="Article 5">
  <data key="d0">Article 5</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 5 is part of a European Union regulation and is associated with Directive (EU) 2016/797 and Regulation (EU) No 1025/2012. It defines specific terms and conditions for AI systems and outlines practices that are prohibited. This article sets requirements for high-risk AI systems and is relevant to multi-stakeholder governance. Article 5 also addresses the legal section that outlines the prohibition of certain AI practices and the associated fines.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-afaeda77e104462626d5a0e5a16d6f4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d534e37e8a91e087b0f7afd91260337&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38169246e9fa46f9e17ff295ac3346d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef9991e58e018e79ec133e41dd155972&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06bc0ddf887512f18d0e6f10df7767fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d3918796c66f4ec90d4e54c0693276f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5303a356a94e477f040c55c8fb0446c1</data>
