<node id="AI literacy">
  <data key="d0">AI literacy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">AI literacy pertains to the knowledge and understanding necessary to operate and use AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6d534e37e8a91e087b0f7afd91260337</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 4">
  <data key="d0">Article 4</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 4 deals with the requirement for providers and deployers to ensure a sufficient level of AI literacy among their staff.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6d534e37e8a91e087b0f7afd91260337</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Biometric Categorisation Systems">
  <data key="d0">Biometric Categorisation Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Biometric Categorisation Systems are tools that categorize individuals based on biometric data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6d534e37e8a91e087b0f7afd91260337</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Facial Recognition Databases">
  <data key="d0">Facial Recognition Databases</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Facial Recognition Databases are collections of facial images used for identification purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6d534e37e8a91e087b0f7afd91260337</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union Harmonisation Legislation">
  <data key="d0">Union Harmonisation Legislation</data>
  <data key="d1">legislation</data>
  <data key="d2">Union Harmonisation Legislation refers to comprehensive legal acts that harmonize rules across the European Union, specifically governing the market and services of AI systems and ensuring the placement of certain products on the market. This legislation covers high-risk AI systems and their conformity assessment procedures, conforming to specific high-risk AI products listed in Annex I. The legal acts are designed to harmonize laws across the European Union, ensuring uniformity in regulations. These acts also address the monitoring requirements for high-risk AI systems, providing a clear framework for their assessment and placement in the market.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e2911d860a9f8426e67a536486d6752&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73bf9d05df7f156f668cf6ea0decb52f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2f70e1025ba333d8cca73e6ed68029e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9aeb5afbd1a4b894acf12c446410f902&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06bc0ddf887512f18d0e6f10df7767fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79168f0d206aaba1ef1cc580415c53cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3235bf9304fec9e624bfd76288a19b57</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Real-Time Remote Biometric Identification Systems">
  <data key="d0">Real-Time Remote Biometric Identification Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Real-Time Remote Biometric Identification Systems are systems used to identify individuals in real-time through biometric data.&lt;SEP&gt;Real-Time Remote Biometric Identification Systems are systems used for biometric identification in publicly accessible spaces for law enforcement purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6d534e37e8a91e087b0f7afd91260337&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Third Countries">
  <data key="d0">Third Countries</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Third Countries are countries that are not part of the European Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Third Countries refers to countries outside the European Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9d94f80b79b953201dabec0b31eb7d1f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2f70e1025ba333d8cca73e6ed68029e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 54">
  <data key="d0">Article 54</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 54 specifies the obligations and responsibilities of authorised representatives of providers of general-purpose AI models.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9d94f80b79b953201dabec0b31eb7d1f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 55">
  <data key="d0">Article 55</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 55 outlines additional obligations for providers of general-purpose AI models with systemic risk.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 55 outlines additional obligations that the codes of practice need to address.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9d94f80b79b953201dabec0b31eb7d1f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 56">
  <data key="d0">Article 56</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 56 encourages and facilitates the drawing up of codes of practice at Union level for the proper application of the Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 56 covers the drawing up of codes of practice by the AI Office to ensure the proper application of the regulation, addressing market and technological developments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9d94f80b79b953201dabec0b31eb7d1f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 75">
  <data key="d0">Article 75</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 75 describes the mutual assistance, market surveillance, and control of general-purpose AI systems by the AI Office.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1f37fb5090b015fdcce5136a4e131a7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89493349bc2eb2b0fa14e08d5114b0a5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 76">
  <data key="d0">Article 76</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 76 details the supervision of testing in real-world conditions by market surveillance authorities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1f37fb5090b015fdcce5136a4e131a7e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 77">
  <data key="d0">Article 77</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 77 outlines the powers of authorities protecting fundamental rights related to high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 77 outlines the roles and responsibilities of national public authorities or bodies.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 77 is a clause within a Regulation and was missed in the previous extraction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1f37fb5090b015fdcce5136a4e131a7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b09e19ff232fc74f764b77ba6bcc3f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5974c0c87096acad0b2aac605ef8802</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Union Law Protecting Fundamental Rights">
  <data key="d0">Union Law Protecting Fundamental Rights</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Union Law Protecting Fundamental Rights includes protections against discrimination.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1f37fb5090b015fdcce5136a4e131a7e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 58">
  <data key="d0">Article 58</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 58 specifies the detailed arrangements for AI regulatory sandboxes, including eligibility criteria, application procedures, and operational conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 58 outlines the provisions for AI regulatory sandboxes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1f37fb5090b015fdcce5136a4e131a7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9a59e2a8b6b3ba9d239dfd8b387900e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Provider">
  <data key="d0">Provider</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The provider is the entity that develops and provides the high-risk AI system.&lt;SEP&gt;Provider is an entity that supplies AI systems and is informed by deployers of incidents.&lt;SEP&gt;Provider is an entity that develops, manufactures, or distributes AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The Provider is a company or organization that develops and intends to place an AI system on the market or put it into service.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4bd0831e0cdcbfe10ebd94d84d35ece&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9aeb5afbd1a4b894acf12c446410f902&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af337ff23074191f5e5e0bdd26073d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64f96fb4c623fd44d4b9931460dfb273&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38169246e9fa46f9e17ff295ac3346d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3235bf9304fec9e624bfd76288a19b57</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Importer">
  <data key="d0">Importer</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Importer is an entity that brings AI systems into a market and is informed by deployers of incidents.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828342</data>
