</node>
<node id="Annex III - Remote biometric identification systems">
  <data key="d0">Annex III - Remote biometric identification systems</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Remote biometric identification systems are a specific type of biometric system, which is intended for the identification of individuals remotely.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-846d247ae92c7dbe167abacc02bc54d4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828343</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Annex III - Biometric categorisation">
  <data key="d0">Annex III - Biometric categorisation</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Biometric categorisation involves the classification of individuals based on sensitive biometric attributes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-846d247ae92c7dbe167abacc02bc54d4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Annex III - Emotional recognition">
  <data key="d0">Annex III - Emotional recognition</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Emotional recognition is a type of high-risk AI system that involves the recognition of emotions through biometric analysis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-846d247ae92c7dbe167abacc02bc54d4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Annex III - High-risk AI systems in critical digital infrastructure">
  <data key="d0">Annex III - High-risk AI systems in critical digital infrastructure</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">High-risk AI systems in critical digital infrastructure are intended to support and operate critical digital infrastructure safely.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-846d247ae92c7dbe167abacc02bc54d4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Annex III - High-risk AI systems in road traffic">
  <data key="d0">Annex III - High-risk AI systems in road traffic</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">High-risk AI systems in road traffic are intended to manage and operate road traffic safely.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-846d247ae92c7dbe167abacc02bc54d4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Annex III - High-risk AI systems in supply of water, gas, heating or electricity">
  <data key="d0">Annex III - High-risk AI systems in supply of water, gas, heating or electricity</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">High-risk AI systems supplying water, gas, heating, or electricity are intended to ensure the safe and reliable operation of these systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-846d247ae92c7dbe167abacc02bc54d4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Seriousness, Probability and Scale of Harm">
  <data key="d0">Seriousness, Probability and Scale of Harm</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Seriousness, probability, and scale of harm refers to the possible harm if the system were not used, evaluated when considering the use of the system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rights and Freedoms of All Persons">
  <data key="d0">Rights and Freedoms of All Persons</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Rights and freedoms of all persons are the rights and freedoms of individuals that the system's use may impact.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Market Surveillance Authority">
  <data key="d0">Market Surveillance Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Market Surveillance Authority is an organization defined under Regulation (EU) 2019/1020, responsible for monitoring compliance with market regulation. It plays a crucial role in overseeing the deployment of AI systems and ensuring they meet necessary standards and requirements. This authority is tasked with authorizing the placing on the market of high-risk AI systems in exceptional circumstances and approving the testing of AI systems and real-world testing plans. According to the regulation, relevant distributors and deployers must inform the Market Surveillance Authority if a high-risk AI system presents a risk or a serious incident. These authorities are also in charge of monitoring the activities of providers and prospective providers to ensure adherence to AI regulations.

The Market Surveillance Authority operates under the oversight of the European Commission and national public authorities, reporting to both the European Commission and national bodies. They can also request support from the Advisory Forum when needed. Essentially, Market Surveillance Authorities are entities within Member States that are responsible for carrying out market surveillance and enforcing AI regulations within their respective national markets, ensuring the safe and lawful deployment of AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7ab695e67854c29668d30835afc8fa56&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c4a20c7ba57c9d3c1ba3d58548d1390&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1653367cdfb434518d14a6c8c5b52df8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64f96fb4c623fd44d4b9931460dfb273&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde5afcadc1bd6c8b37d30bd93e7d045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38169246e9fa46f9e17ff295ac3346d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5974c0c87096acad0b2aac605ef8802&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73bf9d05df7f156f668cf6ea0decb52f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89493349bc2eb2b0fa14e08d5114b0a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79168f0d206aaba1ef1cc580415c53cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e5d3aebe76250dd5161e123f94c06c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ff9251c686ac1ddd5ef4f93316b9a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3235bf9304fec9e624bfd76288a19b57&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f37fb5090b015fdcce5136a4e131a7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment">
  <data key="d0">Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment is a process to assess the impact of the system on the rights and freedoms of individuals.&lt;SEP&gt;Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment is a mandatory process for deploying high-risk AI systems to evaluate potential impacts on fundamental rights.&lt;SEP&gt;Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment is an evaluation of the potential impact of an AI system on fundamental rights such as privacy, security, and equality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-414727d1a6d237ecc9306035920d4685&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af337ff23074191f5e5e0bdd26073d1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Judicial Authority or Independent Administrative Authority">
  <data key="d0">Judicial Authority or Independent Administrative Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Judicial Authority or Independent Administrative Authority is the authority that grants authorizations for the use of the system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Maritime Surveillance Authority">
  <data key="d0">Maritime Surveillance Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Market Surveillance Authority is the authority that oversees market activities and consumer safety.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Protection Authority">
  <data key="d0">Data Protection Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Data Protection Authority is the authority responsible for the protection of personal data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI Practice">
  <data key="d0">AI Practice</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">AI Practice refers to the use of artificial intelligence technology.&lt;SEP&gt;AI Practice refers to specific methods or actions in the context of AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38169246e9fa46f9e17ff295ac3346d7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Annual Report">
  <data key="d0">Annual Report</data>
  <data key="d1">category</data>
  <data key="d2">Annual Report is a report submitted annually to the Commission on the use of the system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c7d4abb8fe7eae2c8001f5fd07e1ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Harmonised Standard">
  <data key="d0">European Harmonised Standard</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Harmonised Standard is a regulation to be demonstrated for alternative means of compliance by the Commission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Codes of Practice">
  <data key="d0">Codes of Practice</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Codes of Practice are documents that need to be developed by the AI Office and Board, encompassing specific issues of information update, detailed summary of content, identification of systemic risks, and their management.&lt;SEP&gt;Codes of practice related to AI model compliance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b23dceb665491f7cc28993744bf6190</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Board">
  <data key="d0">Board</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Board is consulted by the Commission during the standardisation process.&lt;SEP&gt;Board is a framework mentioned in the text where national competent authorities coordinate their activities.&lt;SEP&gt;The Board collaborates with the AI Office to ensure that codes of practice cover specific issues and are proportionate to the risks.&lt;SEP&gt;The Board is the European Artificial Intelligence Board composed of one representative per Member State.&lt;SEP&gt;Board is an organization responsible for advising and assisting the Commission and Member States in the consistent and effective application of the Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;Board is a body mentioned in the context but not further defined.&lt;SEP&gt;The Board is consulted by the AI Office before conducting evaluations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ba7997e7cc9a9c81f53126131569e4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5974c0c87096acad0b2aac605ef8802&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b46993509f7f45efc7114ce53d7712a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef9991e58e018e79ec133e41dd155972&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-351f07fc1cfb91436e9dffcf5c8e88df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f39b62663d19c447e94b4bea8e9c4db</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Trade Secrets">
  <data key="d0">Trade Secrets</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Trade secrets are information or documentation that needs to be handled confidentially according to Article 56.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Civil Society Organisations">
  <data key="d0">Civil Society Organisations</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Civil Society Organisations, industry, academia, and other relevant stakeholders may support the process of creating codes of practice.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Market and Technological Developments">
  <data key="d0">Market and Technological Developments</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Market and technological developments are to be considered for keeping the information up to date as per Article 56.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Systemic Risks">
  <data key="d0">Systemic Risks</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Systemic risks at Union level need to be identified and managed according to the codes of practice.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Key Performance Indicators">
  <data key="d0">Key Performance Indicators</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Key Performance Indicators are used to measure the outcomes of the commitments and measures in the codes of practice.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="General Validity">
  <data key="d0">General Validity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">General Validity refers to the scope of application of the codes of practice within the Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Managerial Responsibilities">
  <data key="d0">Managerial Responsibilities</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The AI Office and Board shall regularly monitor and evaluate the achievement of the objectives and the contribution to the proper application of the regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828344</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulatory Sandboxes">
  <data key="d0">Regulatory Sandboxes</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">AI Regulatory Sandboxes are testing environments established at national or regional levels to foster innovation in AI systems.</data>
