<node id="Member States">
  <data key="d0">Member States</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Member States, referring to countries that are part of the European Union, play a significant role in the context of AI regulation and the operation of AI systems. They are responsible for establishing AI regulatory sandboxes nationally or jointly and are required to adopt their own rules and enforce penalties. Within the framework of the European Union, Member States are represented by a chair in the Board and are requested to provide information to the Commission. The term "Member States" also specifically denotes the countries within the Union that are part of the AI regulatory framework and are involved in the placement of AI systems on the market, putting them into service, or making them available. Member States operate under the legislation of the European Union and are integral to ensuring the harmonized and consistent application of AI regulations across the Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9ca73b5aa4562e502c8b54d80b9091a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d534e37e8a91e087b0f7afd91260337&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95f4bd1a2188c8af0ad581dae55c8d76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b09e19ff232fc74f764b77ba6bcc3f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38169246e9fa46f9e17ff295ac3346d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33b3b690e83a48d4f90c85be3eebb646&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8731e04e59e27f8bf0dad80e14b80dfa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2f70e1025ba333d8cca73e6ed68029e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06bc0ddf887512f18d0e6f10df7767fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af337ff23074191f5e5e0bdd26073d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f39b62663d19c447e94b4bea8e9c4db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6a6be1a6e159da5602b5c2c89e742e39&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b46993509f7f45efc7114ce53d7712a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-351f07fc1cfb91436e9dffcf5c8e88df</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828345</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
