<node id="AI System">
  <data key="d0">AI System</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">An AI System refers to artificial intelligence technology intended for various applications, and is a machine that uses algorithms to perform tasks requiring human-like intelligence. This technology or software is subject to regulations and testing requirements, and can be described as an artificial intelligence system under technical documentation and regulatory guidelines. AI Systems are often required to meet specific standards and quality management systems, particularly when placed on the market or put into service. They include any artificial intelligence technology or application that needs to be registered and documented according to regulatory guidelines.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1f37fb5090b015fdcce5136a4e131a7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e2911d860a9f8426e67a536486d6752&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-612e9d6ebed2e9c1601b0ed553a37ca2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2d5febc258257152890296838762d806&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89493349bc2eb2b0fa14e08d5114b0a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4bd0831e0cdcbfe10ebd94d84d35ece&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-351f07fc1cfb91436e9dffcf5c8e88df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af337ff23074191f5e5e0bdd26073d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-afaeda77e104462626d5a0e5a16d6f4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3235bf9304fec9e624bfd76288a19b57</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828346</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hardware">
  <data key="d0">Hardware</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Hardware refers to physical computing devices and equipment used in conjunction with AI systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-33b3b690e83a48d4f90c85be3eebb646</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828346</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Software Packages">
  <data key="d0">Software Packages</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Software Packages are collections of software that can be installed on a computer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-33b3b690e83a48d4f90c85be3eebb646</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828346</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="APIs">
  <data key="d0">APIs</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">APIs are a means for the Commission to request access to general-purpose AI models.&lt;SEP&gt;APIs are application programming interfaces that allow software components to interact.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-33b3b690e83a48d4f90c85be3eebb646&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b46993509f7f45efc7114ce53d7712a1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828346</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Data Requirements">
  <data key="d0">Data Requirements</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Data Requirements are the specific data needs for an AI system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-33b3b690e83a48d4f90c85be3eebb646</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828346</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Training Data Sets">
  <data key="d0">Training Data Sets</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Training Data Sets are sets of data used to train high-risk AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Training Data Sets are datasets used to train AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Training Data Sets are the datasets used for training the AI system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-33b3b690e83a48d4f90c85be3eebb646&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c328886326bda8019859ce49acc29cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4bd0831e0cdcbfe10ebd94d84d35ece</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828346</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Discriminatory Impacts">
  <data key="d0">Discriminatory Impacts</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Discriminatory Impacts refer to the potential for an AI system to treat individuals unfairly based on their attributes.&lt;SEP&gt;Discriminatory Impacts assess the potential biases and unfair treatment of specific groups by the AI system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-33b3b690e83a48d4f90c85be3eebb646&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-612e9d6ebed2e9c1601b0ed553a37ca2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828346</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Start-ups">
  <data key="d0">Start-ups</data>
  <data key="d1">category</data>
  <data key="d2">Start-ups are considered as part of SMEs and are eligible to participate in AI regulatory sandboxes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9a59e2a8b6b3ba9d239dfd8b387900e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828346</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Articles">
  <data key="d0">Articles</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Articles of the Regulation are legal provisions defining rights, obligations, and procedures, including detailed arrangements and functions of AI regulatory sandboxes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9a59e2a8b6b3ba9d239dfd8b387900e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828346</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 59">
  <data key="d0">Article 59</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 59 details the further processing of personal data for the development of certain AI systems in the public interest within AI regulatory sandboxes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9a59e2a8b6b3ba9d239dfd8b387900e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779828346</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regulation (EU) 2018/1725">
  <data key="d0">Regulation (EU) 2018/1725</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Regulation (EU) 2018/1725 is the Data Governance Act, providing principles and common frameworks for the use of public data.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2018/1725 is the Medical Device Regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;Regulation (EU) 2018/1725 is another data protection regulation.</data>
