<edge source="Commission" target="Notified Body">
  <data key="d7">7.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Notified Bodies must have procedures in place for handling confidential information and take out appropriate liability insurance.&lt;SEP&gt;Notified Bodies shall report any relevant changes to the Commission and other Member States via the electronic notification tool.&lt;SEP&gt;The Commission can authorise conformity assessment bodies from third countries to act as Notified Bodies if they meet the necessary requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;The Commission can suspend, restrict, or withdraw the designation of a Notified Body if they do not meet the requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;The Commission investigates the competence of Notified Bodies and ensures they meet the required standards.&lt;SEP&gt;Notified Bodies must submit reports on their findings to the Commission within a specified period.&lt;SEP&gt;The Commission oversees Notified Bodies and can authorize their activities.</data>
  <data key="d9">authorizations,competence assurance,confidentiality,correction measures,deregistration,harmonisation,insurance,oversight,regulatory compliance,regulatory oversight,report submission,reporting,standardisation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-2cddb0815e714f4234b0eb77a0886db3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd5db792306630e07b4579263bafe09f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8731e04e59e27f8bf0dad80e14b80dfa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e5d3aebe76250dd5161e123f94c06c</data>
